The paper deals with the problem of finding small separators in temporal graphs, which is a topic in graph theory and algorithms. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the planarity of the underlying graph, which suggests cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as a possible sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of the complexity of the problem, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
